obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (28675)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28675&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Dowry Prohibition`
  line `Act, 1961.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 1st July, 1961, vide notification No. S.O. 1410, dated 20th June, 1961, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (28676)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Definition of “dowry”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28676&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, "dowry" means any property or valuable security given or`
  line `agreed to be given either directly or indirectly--`
  line
  line `(a) by one party to a marriage to the other party to the marriage; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the parents of either party to a marriage or by any other person, to either party to the`
  line `marriage or to any other person;`
  line
  line `at or before ^1[or any time after the marriage] ^2[in connection with the marriage of the said parties, but`
  line `does not include] dower or mahr in the case of persons to whom the Muslim Personal Law (Shariat)`
  line applies.
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--The expression "valuable security" has the same meaning as in section 30 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 2, for "or after the marriage" (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `3. The Explanation I omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (28677)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Penalty for giving or taking dowry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28677&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] If any person, after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `gives or takes or abets the giving or taking of dowry, he shall be punishable ^2[with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than ^3[five years, and with fine which shall not be less than fifteen thousand`
  line `rupees or the amount of the value of such dowry, whichever is more]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for adequate and special reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose`
  line `a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than ^4[five years].]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to, or in relation to,--`
  line
  line `(a) presents which are given at the time of a marriage to the bride (without any demand having`
  line `been made in that behalf):`
  line
  line `Provided that such presents are entered in a list maintained in accordance with the rules made`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) presents which are given at the time of a marriage to the bridegroom (without any demand`
  line `having been made in that behalf):`
  line
  line `Provided that such presents are entered in a list maintained in accordance with the rules made`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where such presents are made by or on behalf of the bride or any person`
  line `related to the bride, such presents are of a customary nature and the value thereof is not excessive`
  line `having regard to the financial status of the person by whom, or on whose behalf, such presents are`
  line given.]
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 3 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "six months" (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 3 (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (28678)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Penalty for demanding dowry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 4, for section 4 (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28678&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Penalty for demanding dowry.--If any person demands, directly or indirectly, from the parents`
  line `or other relatives or guardian of a bride or bridegroom, as the case may be, any dowry, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months, but which may extend`
  line `to two years and with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (28679)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Ban on advertisement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 4 (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28679&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Ban on advertisement.--If any person--`
  line
  line `(a) offers, through any advertisement in any newspaper, periodical, journal or through any other`
  line `media, any share in his property or of any money or both as a share in any business or other interest`
  line `as consideration for the marriage of his son or daughter or any other relative,`
  line
  line `(b) prints or publishes or circulates any advertisement referred to in clause (a),`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months, but which`
  line `may extend to five years, or with fine which may extend to fifteen thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for adequate and special reasons to be recorded in the judgment, impose`
  line `a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (28680)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Agreement for giving or taking dowry to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28680&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any agreement for the giving or taking of`
  line `dowry shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (28681)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Dowry to be for the benefit of the wife or her heirs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28681&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any dowry is received by any`
  line `person other than the woman in connection with whose marriage it is given, that person shall transfer it to`
  line `the woman--`
  line
  line `(a) if the dowry was received before marriage, within^1[three months] after the date of`
  line `marriage; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the dowry was received at the time of or after the marriage, within ^1[three months] after the`
  line `date of its receipt; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the dowry was received when the woman was a minor, within ^1[three months] after she has`
  line `attained the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `and pending such transfer, shall hold it in trust for the benefit of the woman.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) If any person fails to transfer any property as required by sub-section (1) within the time limit`
  line `specified therefor ^3[or as required by sub-section (3),] he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than six months, but which may extend to two years or with fine ^4[which`
  line `shall not be less than five thousand rupees, but which may extend to ten thousand rupees] or with both.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where the woman entitled to any property under sub-section (1) dies before receiving it, the heirs`
  line `of the woman shall be entitled to claim it from the person holding it for the time being:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that where such woman dies within seven years of her marriage, otherwise than due to`
  line `natural causes, such property shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if she has no children, be transferred to her parents, or`
  line
  line `(b) if she has children, be transferred to such children and pending such transfer, be held in trust`
  line `for such children.]`
  line
  line `^6[(3A) Where a person convicted under sub-section (2) for failure to transfer any property as required`
  line `by sub-section (1)`
  line `^7[or sub-section (3)] has not, before his conviction under that sub-section, transferred`
  line `such property to the woman entitled thereto or, as the case may be, ^8[her heirs, parents or children] the`
  line `Court shall, in addition to awarding punishment under that sub-section, direct, by order in writing, that`
  line `such person shall transfer the property to such woman or, as the case may be, ^8[her heirs, parents or`
  line `children] within such period as may be specified in the order, and if such person fails to comply with`
  line `the direction within the period so specified, an amount equal to the value of the property may be`
  line `recovered from him as if it were a fine imposed by such Court and paid to such woman or, as the case`
  line `may be, ^8[her heirs, parents or children].]`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this section shall affect the provisions of section 3 or section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 5, for "one year" (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 5 (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "which may extend to ten thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  line
  line `5. The proviso inserted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 5 (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "her heirs" (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (28682)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28682&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. Cognizance of offences.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(a) no Court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) no court shall take cognizance of an offence under this Act except upon--`
  line
  line `(i) its own knowledge or a police report of the facts which constitute such offence, or`
  line
  line `(ii) a complaint by the person aggrieved by the offence or a parent or other relative of such`
  line `person, or by any recognised welfare institution or organisation;`
  line
  line `(c) it shall be lawful for a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class to`
  line `pass any sentence authorised by this Act on any person convicted of an offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "recognised welfare institution or organisation"`
  line `means a social welfare institution or organisation recognised in this behalf by the Central or State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall apply to`
  line `any offence punishable under this Act.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force a statement made by`
  line `the person aggrieved by the offence shall not subject such person to a prosecution under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 6, for section 7 (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 6 (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (28683)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Offences to be cognizable for certain purposes and to be bailable and non-compoundable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=28683&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[[8. Offences to be cognizable for certain purposes and to be bailable and`
  line `non-compoundable.--(1) The Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to offences`
  line `under this Act as if they were cognizable offences--`
  line
  line `(a) for the purposes of investigation of such offences; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the purposes of matters other than--`
  line
  line `(i) matters referred to in section 42 of that Code; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the arrest of a person without a warrant or without an order of a Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) Every offence under this Act shall be ^2[non-bailable] and non-compoundable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `2. Subs. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 7, for section 8 (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 7, for "bailable" (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (30952)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `Burden of proof in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=30952&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Burden of proof in certain cases.--Where any person is prosecuted for taking or abetting the`
  line `taking of any dowry under section 3, or the demanding of dowry under section 4, the burden of proving`
  line `that he had not committed an offence under those sections shall be on him.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (30953)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 11
  title `Dowry Prohibition Officers`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=30953&sectionno=8B&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint as many Dowry`
  line `Prohibition Officers as it thinks fit and specify the areas in respect of which they shall exercise their`
  line `jurisdiction and powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Dowry Prohibition Officer shall exercise and perform the following powers and functions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to see that the provisions of this Act are complied with;`
  line
  line `(b) to prevent, as far as possible, the taking or abetting the taking of, or the demanding of, dowry;`
  line
  line `(c) to collect such evidence as may be necessary for the prosecution of persons committing`
  line `offences under the Act; and`
  line
  line `(d) to perform such additional functions as may be assigned to him by the State Government, or`
  line `as may be specified in the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, confer such powers of a police`
  line `officer as may be specified in the notification on the Dowry Prohibition Officer who shall exercise such`
  line `powers subject to such limitations and conditions as may be specified by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, for the purpose of advising and assisting Dowry Prohibition Officers`
  line `in the efficient performance of their functions under this Act, appoint an advisory board consisting of not`
  line `more than five social welfare workers (out of whom at least two shall be women) from the area in respect`
  line `of which such Dowry Prohibition Officer exercises jurisdiction under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30954)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=30954&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner in which, and the persons by whom, any list of presents referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 3 shall be maintained and all other matters connected therewith; and`
  line
  line `(b) the better co-ordination of policy and action with respect to the administration of this Act.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3)] Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^3[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 63 of 1984, s. 8 (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) renumbered as sub-section (3) thereof by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (30955)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of the State Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1986, s. 9, for section 10 (w.e.f. 19-11-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681&sectionId=30955&sectionno=10&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00003_196128_1517807322681
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Power of the State Government to make rules.--(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the additional functions to be performed by the Dowry Prohibition Officers under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 8B;`
  line
  line `(b) limitations and conditions subject to which a Dowry Prohibition Officer may exercise his`
  line `functions under sub-section (3) of section 8B.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made before the State Legislature.]`
